{"timestamp": "2026-06-18T09:19:17.807206", "query": "what is RAG?", "answer": "RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation, which is the process of optimizing the output of a large language model by referencing an authoritative knowledge base outside of its training data sources before generating a response. It is also a way to make AI answers more reliable by combining searching for relevant information and then generating a response.", "url_hash": null, "retrieved_chunks": [{"chunk_index": 18, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.661512, "rerank_score": 8.858210563659668}, {"chunk_index": 26, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.5876024, "rerank_score": 8.5174560546875}, {"chunk_index": 3, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.6386976, "rerank_score": 7.867913246154785}, {"chunk_index": 0, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/nlp/what-is-retrieval-augmented-generation-rag/", "vector_score": 0.6365199, "rerank_score": 7.4169158935546875}, {"chunk_index": 29, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.5686152, "rerank_score": 6.495140075683594}]}
