{"timestamp": "2026-06-18T09:57:33.680020", "query": "give examples for scatter plot", "answer": "There are two examples of scatter plots provided in the context:\n\n1. A simple scatter plot to visualize the relationship between days and total bill amounts:\n```\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nx = [ 'Thur' , 'Fri' , 'Sat' , 'Sun' , 'Thur' , 'Fri' , 'Sat' , 'Sun' ]\ny = [ 170 , 120 , 250 , 190 , 160 , 130 , 240 , 200 ]\nplt . scatter ( x , y )\nplt . title ( \"Scatter Plot\" )\nplt . xlabel ( \"Day\" )\nplt . ylabel ( \"Total Bill\" )\nplt . show ()\n```\n\n2. A customized scatter plot using diamond-shaped markers, where color represents size, marker size reflects the total bill and transparency is added for better visualization:\n```\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nx = [ 'Thur' , 'Fri' , 'Sat' , 'Sun' , 'Thur' , 'Fri' , 'Sat' , 'Sun' ]\ny = [ 170 , 120 , 250 , 190 , 180 , 130 , 260 , 200 ]\nsize = [ 2 , 3 , 4 , 2 , 3 , 2 , 4 , 3 ]\nbill = [ 170 , 120 , 250 , 190 , 180 , 130 , 260 , 200 ]\nplt . scatter ( x , y , c = size , s = bill , marker = 'D' , alpha = 0.5 )\nplt . title ( \"Customizing Scatter Plot\" )\nplt . xlabel ( \"Day\" )\nplt . ylabel ( \"Total Bill\" )\nplt . show ()\n```", "url_hash": null, "retrieved_chunks": [{"chunk_index": 4, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-visualization/data-visualization-using-matplotlib/", "vector_score": 0.03278688524590164, "rerank_score": 7.5011444091796875}, {"chunk_index": 16, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-visualization/data-visualization-using-matplotlib/", "vector_score": 0.02904040404040404, "rerank_score": 5.166868209838867}, {"chunk_index": 0, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-visualization/data-visualization-using-matplotlib/", "vector_score": 0.028612012987012988, "rerank_score": 1.8330473899841309}, {"chunk_index": 5, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-visualization/data-visualization-using-matplotlib/", "vector_score": 0.03055037313432836, "re