{"timestamp": "2026-06-18T11:28:19.705615", "query": "what is data science?", "answer": "Data science is the study of data used to extract meaningful insights for business decisions. It combines mathematics, computing and domain knowledge to solve real-world problems and uncover hidden patterns.", "url_hash": null, "retrieved_chunks": [{"chunk_index": 0, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.03252247488101534, "rerank_score": 10.341655731201172}, {"chunk_index": 4, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.03200204813108039, "rerank_score": 3.308502197265625}, {"chunk_index": 64, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.032266458495966696, "rerank_score": 0.8041142225265503}, {"chunk_index": 3, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.027529761904761904, "rerank_score": -0.36094027757644653}, {"chunk_index": 1, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.02674825174825175, "rerank_score": -1.0233505964279175}]}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-18T11:28:58.511820", "query": "steps involved in data science", "answer": "The steps involved in data science are:\n1. Data Collection: Gathering raw data from various sources, such as databases, sensors or user interactions.\n2. Data Cleaning: Ensuring the data is accurate, complete and ready for analysis.\n \nAdditionally, other steps mentioned are:\n1. Data Analysis: Applying statistical and computational methods to identify patterns, trends or relationships.\n2. Data Visualization: Creating charts, graphs and dashboards to present findings clearly.\n3. Decision-Making: Using insights to inform strategies, create solutions or predict outcomes.", "url_hash": null, "retrieved_chunks": [{"chunk_index": 0, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.03278688524590164, "rerank_score": 8.469244956970215}, {"chunk_index": 4, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.03200204813108039, "rerank_score": -0.9025717973709106}, {"chunk_index": 3, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.03076923076923077, "rerank_score": -1.7364822626113892}, {"chunk_index": 1, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.028309409888357256, "rerank_score": -2.931313991546631}, {"chunk_index": 64, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.03200204813108039, "rerank_score": -4.117627143859863}]}
{"timestamp": "2026-06-18T11:30:01.179720", "query": "tell me about important skills and increasing demands of data science", "answer": "Important skills in data science include:\n\n1. Programming: Proficiency in programming languages like Python, R or SQL.\n2. Statistics and Mathematics: A strong foundation in statistics and linear algebra.\n\nAs for increasing demand, data science is used for:\n\n1. Decision-Making & Forecasting: Businesses analyze data to identify trends, reduce risks and predict future demand.\n2. Efficiency & Optimization: Helps in saving time and resources by improving processes like supply chain and operations.\n3. Personalization: Enables customized recommendations in platforms like e-commerce and marketing.", "url_hash": null, "retrieved_chunks": [{"chunk_index": 4, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.03278688524590164, "rerank_score": 2.302410125732422}, {"chunk_index": 3, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.031024531024531024, "rerank_score": 0.5953134894371033}, {"chunk_index": 0, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.031754032258064516, "rerank_score": 0.21899887919425964}, {"chunk_index": 2, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.0315136476426799, "rerank_score": -0.8393881320953369}, {"chunk_index": 1, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-science/data-science/", "vector_score": 0.02900988017658188, "rerank_score": -2.3173675537109375}]}
