{"timestamp": "2026-06-18T12:39:31.558134", "query": "explain working of RAG", "answer": "The system first searches external sources for relevant information based on the user’s query instead of relying only on existing training data. Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) is the process of optimizing the output of a large language model, so it references an authoritative knowledge base outside of its training data sources before generating a response. With RAG, an information retrieval component is introduced that utilizes the user input to first pull information from a new data source.", "url_hash": null, "retrieved_chunks": [{"chunk_index": 13, "source_url": "https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/nlp/what-is-retrieval-augmented-generation-rag/", "vector_score": 0.030679156908665108, "rerank_score": 6.82266092300415}, {"chunk_index": 18, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.0315136476426799, "rerank_score": 3.4173645973205566}, {"chunk_index": 3, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.03036576949620428, "rerank_score": 3.237255096435547}, {"chunk_index": 29, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.027271052146674038, "rerank_score": 2.984218120574951}, {"chunk_index": 43, "source_url": "https://aws.amazon.com/what-is/retrieval-augmented-generation/", "vector_score": 0.02625418060200669, "rerank_score": 2.852637529373169}]}
